  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Targeted Ebola preparedness activities in Refugee hosting districts</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this UNHCR project is to strengthen Infection Prevention and Control (IPC) at the refugees&apos; settlements and high-volume health facilities in Kisoro, Kanungu and Kyegegwa. With this CERF grant, UNHCR will procure and distribute Personal Protective Equipment and supplies for a value of $160,000. UNHCR will also construct screening shelters at Bunagana, Nteko, Busanza and Ishasha Points of Entry. the project will last six months and will benefit 1,476,509 people including 737,603 women and girls.</narrative>
  </description>
